    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nVirtual lines above a line where a fold starts show `foldopen` in `foldcolumn`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.cmd('enew')\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, { 'line 1', 'line 2', 'line 3', 'line 4' })\n\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('fold-virt')\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(\n  0,\n  ns,\n  1,\n  0,\n  { virt_lines = { { { 'v Above' } } }, virt_lines_above = true }\n)\n\nvim.o.foldcolumn = '1'\n```\n\n- `nvim --clean -u test.lua`\n- `jzfj` to fold second and third lines\n- `zo` to open the fold\n\nYou should see `foldopen` (`-`) duplicated in the foldcolumn of the virtual line:\n\n<img width=\"505\" height=\"284\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/866a9d15-6c61-496c-91e8-69013431d67c\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`foldopen` should only appear once, on line 2.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.13.0-dev-532+g84d5c5f4bf\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64, Linux 7.0.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20251201-075747-d3b0fdad\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch User Repository (AUR)",
